Things to do:

The language that was provided by William and approved by Sara Shackleton is 
good; unfortunately, however, referencing the currencies in the Product Type 
description creates a situation where we would need a new Product Type with 
each new currency exchanged (something we should not do).   So - I took a 
stab at some 'generic' Product Type language that should allow us to 
introduce other currencies - see attached. Brent Hendry has agreed to look at 
this for us, as Sara is on vacation.

Brent, pay close attention to what's in bold; it's a belt and suspenders 
approach to understanding who pays what, but may be considered redundant.

If we are going to treat this as a Physical Product, then we have the hurdle 
of the 'Location' field to get over. 
Mark Dilworth/Jason Althaus  - for these Products, can we set the Location to 
something like NULL and have the feild pull in no text  (like the Strikes on 
the Options)?  (Something tells me we'll have to resort to something CHEEZY 
!!)

Tomorrow Rob and I are going to try to set up a Conference Call to Amita. I 
need to have a better understanding of what trading wants to offer so that we 
make sure we're representing the right Enron Entity. When we set up the first 
internal FX products, they were done with RMT b/c we knew our only customer 
would be ECC and product would be CAD. I would be surprised if they're aren't 
tax consequences associated with having ETRIC manage ENA Products.

We have not been trained on how the FX Manager works; perhaps someone can 
educate us.

Dale




