Hi ,

Just so that everyone is on the same page:

As it stands now we need to create two internal products (Stack Manager) 
USD/EURO, and USD/JPY, and two Fx link products ( Fx manager) USD/EURO, and 
USD/JPY .  These will be 24 hour products manged by London and Houston Fx 
traders.
To overcome the numeric display issues volume will be in millions of dollars 
and on the USD/JPY Fx link product  we need to find a non-technical solution 
to the number of decimal places that can be displayed both in the FX Manager 
and the website.
We have the legal descriptions required for the internal products and per 
William Sarah has approved them as is. Melba can you please check on it and 
co-ordinate with William on building them.
Metals Traders should work with London Product Control to get the legal 
descriptions and GTC's approved for the mteals products in EURO and JPY
Melba can you please co-ordinate with William and Jason to get the FX link 
products set up in FX Manager . Once they are set up William and Shane should 
co-ordinate with the metals traders to test that the links are working ok. 


Thanks.

Savita








